description: 1944. England is still locked in a struggle to the death with Nazi Germany. But already a new threat looms among the peaks of the Himalayas. For now, though, Squadron Leader Blake, having saved London from a German prototype, is assigned to a top secret mission, during which he meets with an old friend he hasn’t seen since India: Philip Mortimer. Soon, the pair are introduced to an officer working for Allied Intelligence: Colonel Olrik...
name: Plutarch's Staff

THE FIRST FOUR EPISODES OF THE NEW SERIES OF DOCTOR WHO, PREVIEWED IN DWM 491!

Doctor Who Magazine exclusively previews the first four episodes of the new series: The Magician's Apprentice & The Witch's Familiar and Under the Lake & Before the Flood...

Under the Lake and Before the Flood form Toby Whithouse's first two-part Doctor Who story – and it hinges on time travel – and fairly mind-bending time travel at that. While plotting and writing, did Toby ever come to regret taking the wibbly-wobbly, timey-wimey route?

"Oh never, I loved it! I've always wanted to do a timey-wimey episode," he says. "In fact, it was going to be a lot more timey-wimey, but we lost some of that before we started filming. It's enormous fun to deposit something in a script, then have the reason for it happen later."

This is also the first story that Toby's written to star Peter Capaldi as the Doctor.

"I think he's the most 'alien' Doctor we've had since the show came back," says Toby. "Even though the essentials of the character remain the same – his heroism, his brilliance, his enthusiasm – he feels to me like much more of an outsider than Chris Eccleston or David Tennant or Matt Smith were. He's more strange and otherwordly. That's really interesting to play with."

ALSO INSIDE THE BUMPER 100-PAGE ISSUE 491...

  • TARDIS TAKE-OFF!The Doctor's days off and the TARDIS' take off – showrunner Steven Moffat answers readers' questions.
  • CLARA OSWALD'S 100 IMPOSSIBLE FACTS
    She has been something of 'a mystery wrapped in an enigma' but we've got to know Clara better than you might think. Jonathan Morris summarises everything we know about the Impossible Girl.
  • MONSTERS OF THE MILLENNIUM
    How do you go about making monsters for Doctor Who? Millennium FX prosthetic effects supervisor Kate Walshe reveals all!
  • LEGO DIMENSIONS!
    Official Lego products and a brand new video game.... Doctor Who is about to enter a new dimension. DWM talks to the team behind the project.
  • BEST DRESSED TIME LORD
    DWM interviews costume designer Ray Holman, the man behind the Twelfth Doctor's new look.
  • "GOOD GRIEF!"
    As the Third Doctor returns for a brand new series of audio adventures, DWM talks to the man who is recreating the role made famous by Jon Pertwee: Tim Treolar.
  • THE WAR GAMES
    The Fact of Fiction explores the Second Doctor's final story, a 10-part epic which threw the Doctor and his companions back into the events of the First World War.
  • JUNGLE FEVER!
    The adventure continues in the brand-new comic strip adventure, Spirits of the Jungle, by Jonathan Morris, illustrated by John Ross.
  • WHO HOMEWORK
    Jacqueline Rayner makes her kids' summer homework fun with an exciting Doctor Who project in her regular column, Relative Dimensions.
  • MISSING IN ACTION
    Graham Kibble-White reviews The Macra Terror, a Second Doctor story missing from the BBC archives.
  • COMING SOON
    DWM talks to the people involved in the latest Doctor Who CD and book releases, including Justin Richards and Miranda Raison.
  • THE UNEXPLAINED
    The Watcher reflects on past Doctors and anticipates the new series of Doctor Who in Wotcha!.
  • PLUS! All the latest official news, reviews, competitions and The DWM Crossword.
  • AND! A giant-sized, double-sided poster!

The Blue Elves, the Yrlanais and the Dwarves join forces to fight the evil army of the Black Elf necromancer: Lah’saa.

Kastennroc is a legendary impregnable fortress. The Blue Elves and the Yrlanais try to trap the Black Elf Lah’saa and her army of ghouls that have come to invade the land of Arran. The

Elves’ army benefits from the power of the blue crystal and has one of the strongest Arran warriors: Redwin the Dwarf. The war enflames Kastennroc, and no-one knows who will triumph.
name: Kastennroc

description: Translates Invincible #70 and Invincible Returns.
name: Los Problemas Crecen

description: Translates Invincible #85-90.
name: Lazos Familiares

description: Translates Invincible #97-102.
name: La Muerte de Todos
Un gros chien avec une blonde

description:
The whole world is devastated by the plague and the endless war. The human race will almost disappear in the world.

However, there is a young orphan named Danny with tears stains under his eyes, which comes from a small town destroyed by earthquake act as a joker in a circus troupe. In this painful world, he brings hope to people with his happiness…
name: Livre 1

description:
76 Action-Packed Pages in the Mighty Marvel Manner!

An incredible new Thor saga begins! Malekith, Lord of the Dark Elves, is back and blood will flow!

Also: Captain America and the Falcon battle Nuke in a deadly fight to the finish!

Plus: Death's Head returns, and Tony Stark learns just what the heck the Godkiller is!

By Rick Remender, Carlos Pacheco, Kieron Gillen, Greg Land, Jason Aaron and Ron Garney!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Vol.7 #14, Iron Man Vol.6 #13 and Thor: God of Thunder #13!

More action and adventure in the future-shocked world of Judge Dredd! Dredd investigates shady goings-on in the Cursed Earth in "El Maldito" by Gordon Rennie and Carlos Ezquerra; Brit-Cit Psi-Judge Lillian Storm talks with the dead in Storm Warning by Leah Moore, John Reppion and Tom Foster; the carnival’s in town in in "Lawless" by Dan Abnett and Phil Winslade; and has Paul Grist's Demon Nic met his match? Plus the usual interviews, features, and more - and in the bagged graphic novel this month, Freaks by Peter Millgan and John Higgins!

Cover: Carlos Ezquerra

  • Judge Dredd - El Maldito (Part Four) (Gordon Rennie - Carlos Ezquerra)
  • Demon Nic - I Sit and Wait (Part Four) (Paul Grist)
  • Storm Warning - The Relic (Part Four) (Leah Moore - John Reppion - Tom Foster)
  • Lawless - Between Badrock & A Hard Place (Part Four) (Dan Abnett - Phil Winslade)

Graphic Novel - Freaks
name: Meg 364

description:
One scriptwriter, 6 artists, a great people: the Dwarves!
Discover the tragic destiny of Ordo of the Order of the Talion

Ordo is accursed… Born on the sixth day of the sixth moon, he is the sixth child of a family of siblings of the Order of the Talion. On his sixth birthday, his father abandons him to

the instructors of the Black Lodge, a secret branch of the Order which trains assassins destined to eliminate all those who are opposed to the Talion plan. Thirty years later, Ordo has become a Master of the Shadows. The time has come for him to avenge himself on all those who betrayed him and who made him suffer so much.
name: Ordo du Talion

description:
In the heart of the Sixties, Hubert Bonisseur de la Bath, aka OSS 117, will lead you into thundering adventures! Seduction and action are guaranteed!

OSS 117 is an arrogant CIA agent and a confirmed seducer. Sent on a secret mission into the Soviet Embassy in Mexico, he will have to use all his multiple

talents to infiltrate enemy territory and to discover what is really brewing!
name: Tequila Molotov pour OSS 117

description: Manfred Von Richthofen is now flying over Russia, where his missions escorting heavy bombers or strafing ground troops are doing considerable damage. So much so that he’s eventually offered the opportunity to transfer to the Western Front and pit himself against the best British fighters. But a nasty surprise is waiting for him: among his new colleagues is his old enemy Prince Friedrich. The foe in the air may not be the most dangerous one…
name: Dungeons and Dragons

description: After the Spooks' difficult mission in Cuba, Morton Chapel has accepted Kathryn Lennox's help in attempting to treat his daughter, Megan. The girl has been catatonic since she witnessed her father shoot her demented mother Madeleine. But Chapel speaks of possession rather than insanity; an hypothesis the rational Kathryn finds it difficult to accept. And Madeleine's father, a mining industry mogul, intends to exact his revenge from the Spooks leader.
name: Megan

description:
The story of Succubi in the New World is written in letters of blood

New Spain, 1574.

Established in Mexico three years ago, the Inquisition Tribunal burns its first victims on the public square and starts the first auto-da-fé of books. In a rich house not far from there, a young Indian girl gives to Doña Inés an old manuscript belonging to her people, the Codex Veneficiis, the “Book of Spells”.
name: Nayeli

description:
Dive into a pivotal place and era in the history of humanity!

Leaving Lisbon, Cidália arrives in the humid heat of Macao in the spring of 1706. The city is governed jointly by the Portuguese and the Manchu dynasty, the new rulers of China. It is in this troubled and corrupted context that Cidália meets Xue Dan. The two young women each have a difficult mission to accomplish. They decide to join forces, which is a bold idea, but full of dangers…
name: Xue Dan

description: The two Galaxity agents’ investigation into the elemental forces appearing on Earth continues. While Laureline, dogged and efficient, follows a promising lead somewhere in outer space, Valerian is struggling to unravel the mysterious events plaguing our 20th century. Demonstrations of fantastic phenomena follow in quick succession, pushing poor Valerian to his limits. And matters will have to be settled simultaneously in New York and on an asteroid on the edge of the galaxy to save our world...
name: Brooklyn Line, Terminus Cosmos

description: Our 9th compilation for Comixology of Aces Weekly - the award-winning on-screen comic art magazine featuring some of the world's finest creators of comic art. Published by David Lloyd, the guy who brought you V For Vendetta.
name: Volume 09

description: Stretch those laughter muscles as The Dandy Annual returns for another side-splitting serving of jolly japes, crafty schemes and wizard wheezes! With comic legends like Desperate Dan, Winker Watson and Korky the Cat serving up chuckles aplenty, The Dandy Annual is a must-have!

Chapter 2

The war in Europe reaches American shores as Jo and Gideon square off on her farm against the crashed Nazi SS troops.
name: Chapter Two

description: Earth Invasion: Degrees of Separation Harsh penalties are meted out to those whom orchestrated the kidnapping of Pamela Greenberg and Pepe Macias. Meanwhile, Truth Corporation has hired another polemicist and Sean Sulivan is not happy about it. Also, the Kazoops decide to target Noah Company individually.
name: Degrees of Separation

description:
When The Music's Over

John O'Ryan goes out on a routine scientific mission to find crystals for clean energy. During this he finds something unlikely hidden in the rocks that John may regret picking up.
name: When The Music's Over

description:
Desdemona is pregnant, but is hubby Iron Dragon ready to be a dad? His attempt to avoid the inevitable makes him look like a clown... literally. Can Dr. Haynus change him back in time for diaper duty?

PLUS a special TALES FROM THE EVIL INC ARCHIVES: The start of last year's Ul'Thax Proposal storyline!
name: Mom's the Word

description: Four all new crime comics featuring new stories by Ben Passmore and Brigid Deacon and continuations of "The Red Swan" by Pete Toms and Harris Smith and "Poor Little Dum Dum" by Thomas Slattery and Harris Smith. Plus pin-ups by Michel Fiffe (Copra) and Amy Searles. Cover by Josh Burggraf. Action packed from first feverish page to the death drenched end.
name: The Red Swan; Poor Little Dum Dum

description: Happy Cat is a comedic story about a pot smoking house cat that rubs up against politicians and online video game players.

The Cold War

Cryogen has arrived on the scene and is terrorizing the city as she searches for the Lightspeed Enforcers.
name: The Cold War

description:
Tales of Oz

Molly reads each of L. Frank Baum's Oz books! They're... pretty weird.
name: Tales of Oz

description:
New Media

Wanting to expand their audience, the guys hire model Julie to portray their heroine. But, as it turns out, models are pretty expensive.
name: New Media

description:
Endgame

Final issue of Volume One! Out of his depth as his team implodes around him, Quinn confronts the superhuman SMOKE.
name: Endgame

description:
Brothers Out of Bond

After a daring escape from Pharaoh's stronghold, Khenti is back on the run. Now, he races towards the Old Capital where he must meet up with his brother Nekhet if they are to still make it Nubia...and freedom.
name: Brothers Out of Bond

description:
Meet Robert Tresvant and his daughter Robi...

...and then RUN!

Horror Show 2050

R.E.E.P.E.R. Men headquarters, 2050. Deputy Commissioner Reese, is barely alive, thought to be dead from the horror of the first issue. He will find out it's better to be dead than alive in the belly of the most terrifying, secret society. Khrome, tries to comprehend her recent state, but not without a mental assault that continues her psychotic transformation. During the horror show, she realize the murder of the professor and the presumed death of, Deputy Commissioner Reese, may be beyond the normal Chicago city crimes.
name: Horror Show 2050

description:
... journey to the end.

Super villainess, Icicle, returns to Rapid City to get revenge on Coil. While she secretly gathers allies, Coil solidifies his position at the top of the super villain food-chain.
name: ...Journey To the End.

description:
The First Inherits

Samurai are on a hunt for an ancient treasure with mystical properties. During their journey, honor and loyalty are forgotten and replaced by greed and violence. Ultimately, the most courageous warrior must face a new enemy in fortune found.
name: The First Inherits

description: When an expedition to investigate a meteor crash site takes a surprising turn, everyones' favourite hero with an alien strapped on his face Doug Stewart and his team find themselves facing a group of huge alien snake-like shark beasts on a rampage. If that's not bad enough, there's a giant alien egg that starts causing its own brand of chaos. Only one thing is certain.... things are gonna get ugly!

The Glowworm Identity (Special Edition)

"The Glowworm Identity" concludes the Glowworm story arc, resolving the mystery of whether Rob's father, Patrick Hanes, who disappeared when Rob was only a child, was the notorious Cold War era Soviet mole known as Glowworm. This special extended edition also includes as a bonus "The Glowworm Conspiracy," the adventure that kicked off the storyline!
name: The Glowworm Identity

description: "Flights of force are trivial to those who control the wind. Upon my dying, I will still strike thee down." Shepherd 5:1-2

The Trail team, still on a high after their win in the first issue, branch out to follow up on various clues left by Marco Polo back in the 13th century. Clues that relate to an old tradition passed down from generation to generation in Persia that involves the Three Kings and a box they had received from Jesus at his birth. What did the box that the Three Kings receive contain? Did Marco Polo manage to find it? Join the Trail team as they follow in Marco Polo's footsteps in order to unravel the mystery, while unaware that their foes are not as far behind as they had thought.

Attack In The Airless Sea

After a lifetime of guilt and anger over the death of his father at the hands of a greedy space-development corporation, Ambassador Benton Hawkes has broken his vow never to travel off-planet. Reluctantly en route to Mars in the Earth League spaceship Man O' War, he has a new aide for the trip, a woman named Dina Martel, appointed by the duplicitous Senator Mick Carri. Is she someone he can trust? Or a new threat planted by his enemies? The answer may become academic as he now faces a new assassination attempt, looming from the depths of space.
name: Attack In The Airless Sea

description:
Tag! You're It!

Alex's origin revealed!
A wry full-color 10-page summary of Tony Millionaire's doomed attempt to get Billy Hazelnuts onto television. Available exclusively as a FBI MINI.

The very first 2 four-page "Bradleys" story written and drawn by Peter Bagge more than 30 years ago: ultra-crude, bursting energy... and hilarious! Previously available in the out-of-print "Bradleys" comic, now available exclusively as a FBI MINI.
Ti-Girls: Roughs & Rejects is a collection of preliminary and rejected pages for God & Science: Return of the Ti-Girls by Jaime Hernandez. Available now exclusively as a FBI MINI.
Charles Forsman continues his exploration into teenage ennui in this short story following a character from his graphic novel Celebrated Summer. Available exclusively as a FBI MINI.

In this collection of short fantasy stories, strong women battle it out with all their force and wits, but will that be enough to get them out of sticky situations?

Magical girls Chocolat and Pudding are the best dynamic duo team that protects Earth from the forces of Evil. On the way back to school, Pudding notices something fishy and goes to investigate when she is suddenly wrapped up in maniacal Satano's evil den. Pudding then does her best to hold out until her trusted friend Chocolat comes to her rescue...

A high school girl tries to unseat the upper class students from student council, another girl seeks revenge from an oppressive government, rookie wrestling star looks for her missing senpai, a space cop is ambushed by an enemy force, a young boy wakes up and finds out he's transformed into a woman, and a upcoming pop star goes to an audition of her life (and her boyfriend secretly follows).

From high school drama to space invasion, these strong women have much to overcome!

Note: The digital edition (9/15/2015) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Goliath of Gath isn't much of a fighter. Given half a choice, he would pick admin work over patrolling in a heartbeat, to say nothing of his distaste for engaging in combat. Nonetheless, at the behest of the king, he finds himself issuing a twice-daily challenge to the Israelites: "Choose a man. Let him come to me that we may fight. If he be able to kill me then we shall be your servants. But if I kill him, then you shall be our servants." Day after day he reluctantly repeats his speech, and the isolation of this duty gives him the chance to banter with his shield-bearer and reflect on the beauty of his surroundings.

This is the story of David and Goliath as seen from Goliath's side of the Valley of Elah. Quiet moments in Goliath's life as a soldier are accentuated by Tom Gauld's drawing style, which contrasts minimalist scenery and near-geometric humans with densely crosshatched detail reminiscent of Edward Gorey. Goliath's battle is simultaneously tragic and bleakly funny, as bureaucracy pervades even this most mythic of figures. Goliath displays a sensitive wit, a bold line, and a traditional narrative reworked, remade, and revolutionized.
name: HC

description: Lynda Barry's beloved, genre-defying work of “autobifictionalography” One! Hundred! Demons! exploded the comic book medium, ending up on “Best Of” lists from Time Magazine and the Chicago Tribune. In these seventeen vignettes that touch on the scent of people's homes, why babies are the best dancers, and how pretentious exboyfriends are like head lice, Barry brings her demons out to be exorcised. Described as “brutally honest, thoughtful and soulful” by Nick Hornby in the New York Times, One! Hundred! Demons! takes on Barry's childhood with humor and poignancy.
name: HC

description:
Opening Act

Explaining the catalyst for the "Immortal War": The angel Set is imprisoned, by the archangel Ra, while conveying why humans are only worthy to be ruled; the death of David Essex is reviewed; one of the heroes is ambushed.
name: Opening Act

description:
Guadaluhuh?

Low-rent private eye José Amador takes on the cases other detectives can't handle. And he solves the crap out of them. Two-fisted tales of beigey-ness!
name: Guadaluhuh?

description:
In the near future, people upload their memories as a form of social networking, called "Thoughtshare." Special Agent Brenda Bloodworth leads an FBI task force that can enter people's most guarded memories to solve crimes.

In this series preview story, Bloodworth enters the scene of a bank heist gone wrong, and must jump into the Chain of Thoughts to see who is responsible for a mass murder.

This collection features two comic shorts by writer Christopher Reda and artist Hunter Huang!

The Lone Samurai: Unable to find work, a naginata-wielding Ronin travels to a small village to become a true Samurai. When the town strikes gold, he joins an opportunist merchant and his legendary swordsman. But, when he sees the path of greed, he must summon his unique gifts before losing the village - and himself.

The Knight's Challenge: Unimpressed with the competition of his local fighting tournament, a small time peasant asks his King for the chance to receive proper training and gear to prove his superior knowledge of fighting. But, when he realizes the competition is more than training and weapons, he must learn what it really means to entertain a crowd.

volume.name: The Christopher Reda and Hunter Huang Collection

description:
Part One

Following a deadly shootout in an upstate bar, Eddie returns home to the outback town of Durham with a mysterious gunslinger hot on his trail.
name: Part One

description:
Doors and Dreams

Alex Cooper falls into the dream world of Comatose, a world that is part dream, part game; full of action, adventure, and blood thirsty monsters. With the help of his friend Kevin he begins to make his escape from this world, but they soon discover that there is more to this world than meets the eye. Follow Kevin and Alex and their in Comatose.

Chapter 1: Doors and Dreams

Alex falls into the world of Comatose where he meets a warrior named Kevin... and a blood thirsty monster.
name: Doors and Dreams

description: Former government agent Paul Corduroy seeks redemption by taking a job from a unique -- and possibly heavenly -- client.

"Death Saves: Fallen Heroes of the Kitchen Table" collects 17 all-new comic book stories about what happens when fantasy gaming characters run out of hit points. With many years of combined gaming experience between the creators, each comic explores the time-honored tradition of killing player characters in unique, and often unexpected ways.

Some of the tales in "Death Saves" are funny, others tragic, others something else entirely. Every gaming table is different. However, one constant is that the real relationships between players impacts the fantasy characters' fate as much as the dice.
name: Fallen Heroes of the Kitchen Table

description: It all starts here! There's a mysterious new arrival at the base. Who is he and what does he mean for the future of Area 51?

Meet the Fairy Bitches! Enter this world of excess, status hunger, eco-terrorism and sweetness. Eight stories that present the four sisters that make the heart of this sarcastic, darkly humorous book for readers who enjoy a good laugh, satire and some social criticism along with the contrast of cute art and an experimental format.

ONE

The FIST battles a berserker killer and a galactic bounty hunter as the Fighting Tournament of Fighters begins.
name: ONE

description:
Chapter One - The Great Gaping Maw

Pete the meatball and his meatball friends are rudely awakened from a frozen slumber only to be immediately eaten and thrown into a world of acid lakes, dangerous food gangs and... a third thing. Created by D. Bradford Gambles (foodhatesyou.biz)
name: Chapter One: The Great Gaping Maw

description: Get into Comix is an autobiographical love-letter to punk rock and self-publishing, Rendered in a style reminiscent of the Golden Age of the underground comix movement, the story focuses on the author's journey from wallflower-child, to angst ridden teen, to misanthropic adult, and his evolving relationship with music and art.

A drifter is trying to finish one last thing before he can leave this world with a clean conscience. In a post-apocalyptic world riddled with zombies and other perils, what will it actually take for him to obtain this one last goal?

Every new cycle begins with the destruction of the last. For countless millennium, this has been the recognized order of events. And even though there was a struggle amongst Gods for ultimate dominion, there were still rules that needed to be abided. This struggle, these rules...is called The Armageddon.

Yet, this time, those very rules were ignored. There was the introduction of chaos into what used to be a sound process. And because of this a Sage did something that had never been done before, he interjected himself into the process. And unbeknown to him, because of his actions, Armageddon did not conclude, it was just delayed.

IV: Armageddon shows the consequences of his actions.

YOU KNOW THEIR NAMES:

Lucifer...Michael...Gabriel...Enoch...Joshua

Death...War...Pestilence...Famine

NOW LEARN THEIR STORY

The Begining

The Jacket is the protector of a city for of crime, greed, and aliens. This issue will give a preview of what is to come. Also in this issue you will get peeks into two other stories.
name: The Begining

description: K.M. and R.P. are friends. At least according to them. This is a 16 page coming-of-age comic in color, dealing with the nature of creativity as two teenage friends challenge each other to write a novel.

Bullet Time

Falling from Big Ben whilst being chased by a possessed horse from the American Civil War, the time-travelling vigilante Midnight Man has had stranger days.

Can he foil the plans of a malevolent time-spanning cabal, and save humanity in the process?

He might be out of luck, he's possibly out of time, and he's definitely out of his mind.

Get ready for some TEMPORAL. BULLET. ACTION.

Courtesy of Midnight Man.
name: Bullet Time

description:
Molekei, der letzte der Amisch kämpft für die Zukunft der Menschheit. Als Alien Invasoren über die Erde herfallen und Menschen in Gefäße des Bösen verwandeln, ist es an ihm die Sünder zu läutern und das Übel auszumerzen.

Molekei is a warning. Technology makes everything easy today. People carry the wisdom of the world in their pockets but only care about status updates and profile pictures. As alien invaders attack Earth and turn humans into vessels of evil via smart decices, it's on him to punish the sinners and root out all evil.
